newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soymeal ends higher on July Census crush data.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soymeal ends higher on July Census crush data.

text.p: CBOT soymeal futures closed higher on bullish input from the Census Bureau's July crush report, traders said.
The Bureau said U.S. soymeal stocks in July totaled 248,381 tons, down from 358,193 tons in June.
Some support to soy products also came from a late rally in soybeans due to bullish input from a Midwest crop tour.
But soyoil futures closed lower because Census said the July soyoil stocks were at 833.9 million lbs, up from 781.6 million in June.
Soymeal futures volume was estimated at 22,000 contracts, down from 29,084 Wednesday, according to the CBOT. Soymeal options volume was estimated at 1,600 contracts, down from 1,962 Wednesday.
Soyoil futures volume was estimated at 15,000 contracts, up from 12,718 Wednesday. Soyoil options volume was estimated at 500 contracts, down from 1,307 Wednesday.
Soymeal closed $3.70 per ton higher to $4.00 lower, with September up $3.40 at $259.10 a ton. Soyoil closed 0.05 to 0.15 cent per lb lower, with September down 0.13 at 24.99 cents.
